Package entities

Class MenuItem

java.lang.Object
entities.MenuItem
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class MenuItem extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a menu item in a restaurant's menu, from the Supplier's view. Implements Serializable to allow the object to be serialized.
Version:
August 2024
Author:
Kfir Amoyal, Israel Ohayon, Yaniv Shatil, Noam Furman, Omri Heit, Eitan Zerbel

    • MenuItem

      public MenuItem(int itemId, int restaurantId, String name, String description, float price, String category, String possibleChanges)
      Constructs a new MenuItem with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      itemId - the unique identifier for the menu item
      restaurantId - the unique identifier for the restaurant
      name - the name of the menu item
      description - a description of the menu item
      price - the price of the menu item
      category - the category of the menu item (e.g., appetizer, main course)
      possibleChanges - any possible changes that can be made to the menu item
